Small Disc-mill Head

The 335.14 range offers new options of small diameter disc cutters from Ø9,7mm, particularly suitable for small and light machines and multi-task machining centers. The 335.14 products line are here to ensure you can achieve the productivity and profitability you need in any small disc milling application.

Specifications:

  • Small-diameter disc cutters with reliable exchangeable carbide head systems
  • Ideal for groove milling, circlip grooves, full radius profiles and top and bottom chamfering
  • Precise cutting profile easily tackles any type of material and operation
  • Cutter diameters from 9.7 to 34.7 mm (0.38inch to 1.36inch)
  • Cutting widths from 0.7 to 5.15 mm (0.027inch to 0.20inch)
  • Exchangeable heads with three or six teeth
  • Wide selection of cylindrical shanks made of steel and carbide
  • Integrated collet chuck shanks also available
